      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/50/4",
      "text": [
        " سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ أَوْ سَمِعْتُهُ يَقُولُ : \"لاَ تُجْبَرُ اَلْحُرَّةُ عَلَى رَضَاعِ اَلْوَلَدِ وَ تُجْبَرُ أُمُّ اَلْوَلَدِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3510 - Sulaiman ibn Dawud Al-Minqari narrated from Abdul Aziz ibn Muhammad, who said: I asked Abu Abdullah (as), or I heard him say:\n\"A free woman is not compelled to breastfeed the child, but an Umm al-Walad (a female slave who bore her master a child) is compelled.\""
        ]
      }
    },
